Spur Corporation released a disappointing sales update on Monday for the six months ending December, which shows that franchise restaurant sales declined by 3% in SA. The company’s share price was 1.5% down at 13h26 on Monday, trading at R27.58. Warren Thompson discussed what has been happening with the company with Rowan Williams from Nitrogen Fund Managers on the Moneyweb @ Midday show. Listen to their conversation below: